\lambda
\sin^2x+\cos^2x=1
(\cos\alpha-\lambda)^2+\sin^2\alpha=0
\lambda^2-2\lambda\cos\alpha+1 = 0
\lambda=\cos\alpha\pm\sqrt{\cos^2\alpha-1}.
\lambda = \cos\alpha\pm i\sin\alpha
\sqrt{\cos^2 \alpha - 1} = \sqrt{-(1-\cos^2 \alpha)} = \sqrt{- \sin^2\alpha} = i\sqrt{\sin^2\alpha}
\lambda=\cos\alpha\pm\sqrt{\cos^2\alpha-1} = \cos \alpha \pm i\sin\alpha
\lambda=\cos\alpha\pm\sqrt{\cos^2\alpha-1}=\cos\alpha\pm\sqrt{(-1)(1-\cos^2\alpha)}=
=\cos\alpha\pm\sqrt{(-1)\sin^2\alpha}=\cos\alpha\pm\sqrt{(-1)}\cdot\sqrt{\sin^2\alpha}=
=\cos\alpha\pm i\sin\alpha
